$ SQL*Plus: set exitcommit
@ set exitcommit

`set exitcommit on` causes → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus to → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/TCL/commit[commit] the current
→ development/databases/Oracle/architecture/transaction when an SQL*Plus session is terminated with the → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/exit[`exit`] command.
-
`set exitcommit off` causes it to be rolled back.


{ set exitcommit off

  gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQLPlus/set/exitcommit/exit_commit_off.sql||

}
{ set exitcommit on

  gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQLPlus/set/exitcommit/exit_commit_on.sql||

}
{ select statement

  gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQLPlus/set/exitcommit/select.sql||

}
{ run.bat: start sql statements

  gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQLPlus/set/exitcommit/run.bat||
}

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus
